A  pupil  at Northcliff High School died on Monday, apparently after collapsing on the school’s sports field. The incident was confirmed by  Gauteng education department spokesperson Steve Mabona. “Yes, we can confirm [it]. We await a formal report,” Mabona told TimesLIVE. TimesLIVE understands  the incident happened while the girl was playing cricket. Paramedics were apparently called to the scene where  she was  certified dead. This is a developing story. TimesLIVE Support independent journalism by subscribing to the Sunday Times. Just R20 for the first month.